## 👤 About Me

Research Data Analyst & Monitoring and Evaluation Professional with over three years’ experience in managing, analyzing, and reporting complex datasets across health research, child welfare, and USAID-funded programs. 

Skilled in data management, statistical analysis, program evaluation, dashboard development, data quality assurance, and research reporting. 

Experienced in supporting studies involving 6,500+ beneficiaries, improving reporting efficiency by 40%, reducing manual data validation workload by 60%, and developing automated analytics solutions using R, R-Shiny, SQL, Excel, KoboToolbox, and Power BI.  

My work focuses on improving data quality, automating reporting systems, and building tools that support evidence-based decision-making in development programs.

